      "text": "The Air Acolytes were founded in 101 AG from the members of the Official Avatar Aang Fan Club. Aang himself taught the members of the group the ways of the Air Nomads and christened them the \"Air Acolytes\", rather than a mere fan club."
    },
    {
      "body": "A small group of Air Acolytes consisting of ${link_0}, ${link_1}, and ${link_2} traveled with Aang and ${link_3} the next year in an attempt to revive ${link_4}, a celebration of the coexistence of human and spirit which had been defunct since the ${link_5}. The group instead noticed that the sacred land had become host to a town which contained the ${link_6}, a mining operation for the grounds' mineral supply. Aang and the Acolytes tried to celebrate the festival nonetheless, but were forced to return to the mine due to continuous earthquakes and a cave-in of the underground facility. They helped treat injured workers following their rescue and also distributed food to them after the spirit General ${link_7} destroyed the refinery but was defeated by Aang. Shortly afterward, the Air Acolytes assembled at the ${link_8} for meditation classes with Avatar Aang. The group returned to the factory town several months later in order to participate in the parade for the ${link_9} with a new recruit, ${link_10}.",
